&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a id="user-content-description" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#description"&gt;&lt;svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;dhtproto&lt;/code&gt; is a library that contains the protocol for the Distributed Hash
Table (DHT), including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The DHT client (&lt;code&gt;src.dhtproto.client&lt;/code&gt;).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Base classes for the protocol handling parts of the DHT node
(&lt;code&gt;src.dhtproto.node&lt;/code&gt;).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A simple, "fake" DHT node, for use in tests (&lt;code&gt;src.fakedht&lt;/code&gt;).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A turtle env extension (&lt;code&gt;src.turtle.env.Dht&lt;/code&gt;) providing a fake DHT node for
use in tests, including methods to inspect and modify its contents.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A thorough test of the DHT protocol, using the client to connect to a node.
The test is run, in this repo, on a fake node, but it can be reused in other
repos to test real node implementations. (&lt;code&gt;src.dhttest&lt;/code&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
